SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04187357
Version: 1

HPSBST02980 rev.1 - HP Array Configuration Utility, HP Array Diagnostics
Utility, HP ProLiant Array Diagnostics and SmartSSD Wear Gauge Utility
Running on Linux, Local Elevation of Privilege

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2014-04-07
Last Updated: 2014-04-07

Potential Security Impact: Local elevation of privilege

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified in HP Array
Configuration Utility, HP Array Diagnostics Utility, HP ProLiant Array
Diagnostics, and SmartSSD Wear Gauge Utility running on Linux. The
vulnerability could be exploited locally resulting in elevation of privilege.

References: CVE-2013-6216, SSRT101452

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP Array Configuration Utility, HP Array Diagnostics Utility, HP ProLiant
Array Diagnostics, and SmartSSD Wear Gauge Utility Software v9.40 or earlier
for Linux

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2013-6216    (AV:N/AC:L/Au:N/C:P/I:N/A:N)       5.0
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

The Hewlett-Packard Company thanks Portcullis Advisories for reporting
CVE-2013-6216 to security-alert@...com.

RESOLUTION

HP Array Configuration Utility, HP Array Diagnostics Utility, HP ProLiant
Array Diagnostics, and SmartSSD Wear Gauge Utility Software v9.40 was the
last supported release for those products. HP recommends migrating to HP
Smart Storage Administrator, or HP Smart Storage Administrator Diagnostic
Utility which are not impacted by this vulnerability.

HISTORY
Version:1 (rev.1) - 7 April 2014 Initial release

Third Party Security Patches: Third party security patches that are to be
installed on systems running HP software products should be applied in
accordance with the customer's patch management policy.

